<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-15T06:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-15T06:29:00-05:00" n="42" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d42">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.002/46</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-15T14:00:00+02:31">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 15, 1917, 2 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1289. <persName corresp="#p_MPN1">Milyukov</persName> resigned,
                                    <persName corresp="#p_TMI1">Tereshchenko</persName> appointed
                                Minister of Foreign Affairs, <persName corresp="#p_KAF1">Kerensky</persName> appointed Minister of War. No appointment
                                yet to Ministry of Finance or Ministry [of] Justice. <persName corresp="#p_KAF1">Kerensky</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_TMI1">Tereshchenko</persName> both favor vigorous
                                prosecution of war. It is believed these appointments will result in
                                coalition cabinet in which workmen’s committee favor offensive
                                warfare which it is thought will be waged aggressively under
                                reformed government.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>